def morphological_denoise(im, kernel_open=(3,3), kernel_close=(5,5)):
    
    kernel = np.ones(kernel_open, np.uint8)
    opening = cv2.morphologyEx(im, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel) ## Opening

    kernel = np.ones(kernel_close, np.uint8)
    closing = cv2.morphologyEx(opening, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel)

    return closing

plt.figure(figsize = (15, 20) )

clean_images = []
measure = []

for index, images in enumerate(new_images):
    img = images * 1 

    canny = cv2.Canny(img, 250, 255, L2gradient=True)

    tested_angles = np.linspace(-np.pi/2, np.pi/2, 180)
    h, theta, d = hough_line(canny, theta=tested_angles)
    h, theta, d = hough_line_peaks(h, theta, d, num_peaks=1)

    for angle, dist in zip(theta, d):
        a = np.cos(angle)
        b = np.sin(angle)
        (x0, y0) = dist * np.array([np.cos(angle), np.sin(angle)])
        x1 = int(x0 + 100*(-b))
        y1 = int(y0 + 100*(a))
        x2 = int(x0 - 440*(-b))
        y2 = int(y0 - 440*(a))

        # Interpolate values from the neighborhood in img
        x_values = np.linspace(x1, x2, num=1000, endpoint=True).astype(int)
        y_values = np.linspace(y1, y2, num=1000, endpoint=True).astype(int)
        size = 13
        for x, y in zip(x_values, y_values):
            neighborhood = img[y - size//2:y + size//2 + 1, x - size//2:x + size//2 + 1]
            color = tuple(map(int, np.median(neighborhood, axis=(0, 1))))
            cv2.line(img, (x, y), (x, y), color, 5)

    rad = np.arange(80, 180)
    h = hough_circle(canny, radius=rad)
    accum, cx, cy, rad = hough_circle_peaks(h, radii= rad - 30, min_xdistance=10, min_ydistance=10, threshold=0.20, total_num_peaks= 1)
    measure.append(np.array([int(cx), int(cy)])) 

    for center_y, center_x, radius in zip(cy, cx, rad):
        cv2.circle(img, (center_x, center_y), radius, (0, 0, 0), thickness=-1)
    clean_images.append(img)
        
    plt.subplot(5, 3, index + 1)
    plt.imshow(img)

plt.show()

clean_images = np.stack(clean_images, axis=0)
measure = np.stack(measure, axis=0)

for index, old_image in enumerate(new_images):

    heigh, width,_ = old_image.shape

    img_warpolar = cv2.warpPolar(src = old_image, dsize = (0, 0), center = center, maxRadius= max_radius, flags= cv2.WARP_POLAR_LINEAR)

    image_center = (heigh // 2, width /2) 
    max_radius = np.sqrt(((int(heigh // 2)/2.0)**2.0)+(( int(width /2)/2.0)**2.0))
    out_back = cv2.warpPolar(img_warpolar, center=image_center, maxRadius=max_radius, dsize=(heigh, width),flags=cv2.WARP_INVERSE_MAP + cv2.WARP_POLAR_LINEAR)

    img_HSV = cv2.cvtColor(out_back, cv2.COLOR_RGB2HSV)

    HSV_new = cv2.merge([h, s, v_new])
    img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(HSV_new, cv2.COLOR_HSV2RGB)
    img_gray = cv2.cvtColor(img_rgb, cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)
    _, mask_img = cv2.threshold(img_gray, 0, 1, cv2.THRESH_BINARY_INV)

plt.figure(figsize = (15, 20) )

Area_img = []
processed_img = []
out_warpolar = []

for (index, images), mask_orig in zip(enumerate(clean_images), mask_original):
    img = images * 1 

    heigh, width, _ = img.shape 

    cx, cy = measure[index] 
    center = (int(cx), int(cy))
    max_radius = np.sqrt(((int(cx)/2.0)**2.0)+(( int(cy)/2.0)**2.0))
    img_warpolar = cv2.warpPolar(src = img, dsize = (0, 0), center = center, maxRadius= max_radius, flags= cv2.WARP_POLAR_LINEAR)

    out0  = cv2.GaussianBlur(img_warpolar, (19, 19), 0)
    ret, mask = cv2.threshold(out0, 30, 255, 0)
    mask = cv2.cvtColor(mask, cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)

    contours, hierarchy = cv2.findContours(mask, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_NONE)

    final_contours = []
    for contour in contours:
        area = cv2.contourArea(contour)
        if area > 500:
            final_contours.append(contour)

    filtered_contours = []

    for contour in final_contours:
        points = contour[:, 0, :]  # Extracting the contour points
        row_max = np.where(points[:, 1] == img_warpolar.shape[0] - 1 ) ## we will take the first one value that equal the hight from img_warpolar image
        row = np.arange(0, np.min(row_max) )
        points = points[row, :]
        for point in points:
            filtered_contours.append(point + 2)

    filtered_contours = np.stack(filtered_contours, axis=0) ## Here we are already able to claculate Radius, area, appearance, degree of circularity.

    img_warpolar_red = img_warpolar * 1 ### to get the same than img_warpolar but without the red contours
    for row in filtered_contours:
        x, y = row[0], row[1]
        cv2.line(img_warpolar_red, (x, y), (x, y), (255, 0, 0), 4)

    # Create an empty mask
    mask = np.zeros(img_warpolar.shape[0:2], dtype=np.uint8)
    filtered_contours = np.vstack([(img_warpolar.shape[1], 0), filtered_contours])
    filtered_contours = np.vstack([filtered_contours, (img_warpolar.shape[1], img_warpolar.shape[0])])

    cv2.fillPoly(mask, [filtered_contours], color=1)
    mask_channel = cv2.merge((mask, mask, mask))

    out_red = cv2.multiply(img_warpolar_red, mask_channel) ### All the ROI will be black 
    out = cv2.multiply(img_warpolar, mask_channel) ### All the ROI will be black
    out_warpolar.append(out)

    image_center = (heigh // 2, width /2) 
    max_radius = np.sqrt(((int(heigh // 2)/2.0)**2.0)+(( int(width /2)/2.0)**2.0))
    out_back_withRed = cv2.warpPolar(out_red, center=image_center, maxRadius=max_radius, dsize=(heigh, width), flags=cv2.WARP_INVERSE_MAP+cv2.WARP_POLAR_LINEAR)
    out_back_withoutRed = cv2.warpPolar(out, center=image_center, maxRadius=max_radius, dsize=(heigh, width), flags=cv2.WARP_INVERSE_MAP+cv2.WARP_POLAR_LINEAR)
    processed_img.append(out_back_withoutRed)
    
    mask_back = cv2.warpPolar(mask_channel, center=image_center, maxRadius=max_radius, dsize=(heigh, width), flags=cv2.WARP_INVERSE_MAP+cv2.WARP_POLAR_LINEAR)
    area_img = cv2.bitwise_or(mask_back[:,:,2], mask_orig)
    area_img = morphological_denoise(area_img, kernel_open=(3,3), kernel_close=(5,5))
    Area_img.append(area_img)

    plt.subplot(5, 3, index + 1)
    plt.imshow(out_back_withRed, cmap='gray')
    # plt.imshow(out, cmap='gray')

plt.show()

Area_img = np.stack(Area_img, axis=0)
processed_img = np.stack(processed_img, axis=0)

plt.figure(figsize = (15, 20) )

for index, area_img in enumerate(Area_img): 
    binary_img = 1 - area_img 
    contour, _ = cv2.findContours(binary_img, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
    mask_channel = cv2.merge((binary_img * 255, binary_img * 255, binary_img * 255))
    cv2.drawContours(mask_channel, contour, -1, (255, 0, 0), 3)

    contour = contour[0]

    area = cv2.contourArea(contour)
    perimeter = cv2.arcLength(contour, closed=True)
    radius = np.sqrt(area / np.pi)
    circularity = (4 * np.pi * area) / (perimeter**2)

    # Overlay information on the image
    text = f" \n Radius: {radius:.2f} \n Area: {area:.2f} \n Perimeter: {perimeter:.2f} \n Circularity: {circularity:.2f}"
    for i, line in enumerate(text.split('\n')):
        cv2.putText(mask_channel, line, (10, 5 + i * 50), cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 1, (255, 255, 255), 3, cv2.LINE_AA)

    plt.subplot(5, 3, index + 1)
    plt.imshow(mask_channel)

img = out_warpolar[10] * 1

plt.figure(figsize = (5, 10) )

# cv2.getGaborKernel(ksize, sigma, theta, lambda, gamma, psi, ktype)
ksize_ = 20 # - size of gabor filter (n, n)
sigma_ = 10 # - standard deviation of the gaussian function
theta_ = np.radians(90) # range(0, 180, 45) - orientation of the normal to the parallel stripes
lambda_ = 22 # range(5, 15, 5) - wavelength of the sunusoidal factor
gamma_ = 0 # range(0.5, 1, 0.1) - spatial aspect ratio
psi_ = 0 # np.radians(90)# range(0, 180, 45) - phase offset
# ktype_ = # - type and range of values that each pixel in the gabor kernel can hold

g_kernel = cv2.getGaborKernel((ksize_, ksize_), 
                                  sigma_, 
                                  theta_, 
                                  lambda_, 
                                  gamma_, 
                                  psi_, 
                                  ktype=cv2.CV_32F)

img_gray = cv2.cvtColor(img.copy(), cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)
filtered_img = cv2.filter2D(img_gray, cv2.CV_8UC3, g_kernel)

_, binary_img = cv2.threshold(filtered_img, 200, 1, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)


plt.imshow(binary_img )

plt.show()
